						<summary>

						<p>The inscription which is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 834, Śrīmukha, Jyēshṭha, ba. 2, Thursday, Uttarāshāḍha</hi> (= Probably <hi rend="bold">A.D. 912, June 4, Thursday</hi>) refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Akālavarsha (i.e., Kṛishṇa II).</hi> Śrīmukha is probably quoted by mistake for Āṅgirasa. The record which is much damaged seems to record a gift of <hi rend="italic">gōsāsa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
